		<hr size="1">ok took my little warrior to OT other night in a group near the SF ramp.  group was Monk, cleric, chanter, wiz, and me.  for a short bit we were lucky and picked up a 2nd cleric.  that was nice to have.</P><P>anyways my question here is how do i maintain agro from the monk if even after FD a few hits later he has built up enough agro to take it from me again.</P><P>yes i mash the taunt button, and was DW at the time with my fastest weapons.  not ubb3r mind you, but im ok.</P><P>there were several times we played pingpong thanks to the chanter or the wiz(90% of the time it was chanter) pulling agro, then imidiatly sitting down.</P><P>i am now 30th.  i had many more HP then the monk so we tried FD taggin to turn mob on me, but that only worked about 40% of the time longer then 2 or 3 rounds after he/she stood up and attacked the mob again.</P><P>anything other then levels and better weapons i can do, or is this just something were the group members did not care/understand importance of letting the warrior tank?</P><P><hr><font style=font-size:8pt color=yellow>*Worlds worst speller*<BR><font color=yellow><BR>"For those who believe, then no proof is needed.  For those who are skeptics, then no proof will suffice."<font color=00FFFF><BR>"Pigs get fat, but Hogs get slaughtered and VI is a big HOG."<BR><font color=yellow> "So, reading some of my posts is sort of like having sex in your parents house???"  Dr. Zin</P><P></font><BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
