		<hr size="1">Rogues <I>are</i> the highest damaging melee class - it's been proven.  However, monks are not too far away from them.</P><P>The above info is good...the monk probably was just twinked with some better gear.  Warriors are very limited in their methods to gain aggro.  Taunt, SIT (a lot of people forget this method), and weapons.</P><P>Proc'ing weapons are very good for aggro, especially if they are a stunning proc - more aggro from stun than DD (trust me, I'm a Paladin <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/wink.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle>).</P><P>When the mob runs at a sitting caster, sit down immediately.  It will come for you.  If you can, hit taunt at that exact second as well.</P><P>Secret with taunt that many melee don't realize.  It doesn't add to aggro...it immediately puts you at the top of the hate list, if successful.  You don't need to keep hitting it every time it refreshes.  Use it for the moment you lose aggro or if you happen to see the nuker casting, wait for it to land and hit taunt.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
