		<hr size="1">/CLAP Nos, Woohoo!</P><P>TAUNT Button - Nos it makes me very happy that someone else understands the taunt button. Unfortunately SONY doesn't make this clear in any sort of documentation so it is widely misunderstood. Basically, Taunt puts you one point above the highest person on the hate list, IF the taunt is successful. So, instead of repeatedly mashing on taunt as most warriors do, just hit the button when you lose agro to get it back...What Nos said. I have to admit, I often forget about the sitting thing but that is tricky.</P><P>Agro with warriors - Unfortunately in a lot of cases it is the responsibility of other classes to GIVE the warrior agro, other classes should make adjustments for the warrior because the Warrior can be more efficient for the healer.</P><P>DON'T count on Procs - Hate list increasing procs are great and DD damage procs can help. BUT, if a Monk, Rogue(if not using evade) or Ranger comes along and they have good procing weapons they will take agro from you. But remember each of these classes can help the situation (rogue - evade) (Monk FD) (Ranger Jolt).</P><P>Lleb, what is your taunt skill at it sounds like that may be part of the problem. Sounds like your taunt attempts are not successful. Give some time for the skill to increase.</P><P>****EDIT<BR>Sorry Lleb misread the question about FD pulling but going to leave the section below in anyway.<BR>****End Edit<BR>FD Pulling - From what you describe I almost BET that the FD pulling was done incorrectly. Many Noob monks will hit a mob pull it right up close to group and FD. Well, in this case, the closest person or the Medding caster is going to get wacked. So yes, it probably didn't work well. WHAT FD PULLER SHOULD DO - The mob should be pulled a little further away from the party and the tagger should move up close to the mob being pulled. When the Monk FD's the mob should stand their (tagger just out of mob agro range) and not agro anyone, the tagger should then use a bow and shoot the mob pulling it to the group. </P><P>I have had plenty of Monks pull mobs up to the party and FD right by me(shaman) and it makes me mad. Usually, I will tell them what to do and things go perfectly well and they appreciate the tip.</P><P>IMO having a Monk puller for planes groups is an ABSOLUTE necessity! I rarely group without a monk. </P><P></P><P>Message edited by: Jobeker (7/22/2003 11:00:53 AM)</P><P>Message edited by: Jobeker (7/22/2003 11:07:21 AM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
