		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=72&FN=Warrior&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1999628&TN=maintaining+agro+HOW&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2004891&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Get something that procs a debuff/snare/stun or pure hate.  There's no way you can compete against twinks using straight dps for aggro.  Centi LS and lammy both have decent ratios for lower lvls but lack of a proc means you're using straight dps for aggro.  Now compare this to the twinked monk who probably has better ratio weapons then you.  If you get a head start on the mob as in waiting to call assist for a bit, sure you'll have a head start but you're just putting out pure dps.  The monk joins in and will end up right on or ahead of you on the hate list just cause he's out dps'ing you.  The only way around that really is to get high on the hate list by taunting off say a debuffer who gets really high on the hate list from say resisted slows/slows/tash as a succesful taunt will raise you to their lvl of hate +1.  Otherwise if you're on the top of the hate list the whole time even after debuffing a mob, that means the monk will be catching up on you.</P><P>It's sometimes nice when the debuffer pulls a lot of aggro and you're able to pull it off with one succesful taunt because for example(using random numbers) everyone starts at 0 hate, you engage, dps is building you up on the hate list to say 300 points of hate, the chanter tashes raising their hate up to 250, then imediatly slows increasing the hate to 600 points while you're still at 300 hate.  Immediatly as you see so-and-so slows down or yawns you press taunt and it's succesful, you will now have gained 301(using the current theory on taunt) points of hate giving you a nice margin among the others in the group as you continue to build aggro as do they but you've already created that gap.</P><P>Just make sure you're not mashing taunt.  You pull, mob is tashed, press taunt, mob is slowed, press taunt, after that don't press taunt unless the mob turns away from you or is obviously not hitting you.  I look for casting emotes to time taunts after nukes and such but usually by the time casters are nuking aggro is built significantly, usually the most problems you'll see are during debuffing on engagement.  The pain with taunt those is with melee, say the mob turns on the monk, you taunt it turns back but then the monk just out dps's you again pulling aggro back, you have to wait another 6 secs or whatever to taunt again creating ping pong.  My advice would be get a nice proc'ing weapon like frostbringer, wavecrasher, sarnak warhammer(maybe battlehammer, whichever procs stun), silken whip of ensaring or something along the lines of a debuff proc to get the edge on aggro over high dps classes.  Sorry if some of this stuff was mentioned already, just skimmed over the posts.<BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
